        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Polish Workboard operations view",
        "body": "## Summary\n- polish Workboard card layout, timestamps, density controls, detail drawer behavior, mobile modal/dropdown behavior, and tooltip handling\n- add health summary badge highlighting, filter-aware views, stable card action slots, card-derived agent filter options, and better empty states\n- add guarded Workboard auto-refresh with dispatch-safe refresh sequencing, stale refresh protection, and disconnect cleanup\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/dom-tooltips.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/workboard.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/workboard.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-settings.refresh-active-tab.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-lifecycle.node.test.ts`\n- `node --import tsx scripts/control-ui-i18n.ts check`\n- `pnpm tsgo:test:ui`\n- `pnpm --dir ui build`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.ui-e2e.config.ts --configLoader runner ui/src/ui/e2e/workboard.e2e.test.ts ui/src/ui/e2e/workboard-status-persistence.e2e.test.ts`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` clean: no accepted/actionable findings\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: Workboard operations view layout, filters, health badges, tooltip-safe card actions, custom dropdowns, edit/create modals, drag/reload flow, and read-only behavior after the Phase 1 polish changes.\n\nReal environment tested: Local Control UI Vite server with Playwright Chromium and a mocked Gateway WebSocket, running from the rebased PR branch at `b86dfdabb3eea4dcdf3ce86a31493aca116bded6`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n```sh\nPATH=\"/Users/jason/.nvm/versions/node/v24.14.0/bin:$PATH\" node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.ui-e2e.config.ts --configLoader runner ui/src/ui/e2e/workboard.e2e.test.ts ui/src/ui/e2e/workboard-status-persistence.e2e.test.ts\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: The browser proof run passed `2` Workboard E2E files and generated local visual artifacts. Screenshots: `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/workboard/01-empty-board.png`, `02-create-dialog.png`, `03-created-card.png`, `04-edited-card.png`, `05-moved-running.png`, `06-lifecycle-review.png`, `07-reloaded-review.png`, `08-read-only-board.png`, plus `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/workboard-status-persistence/workboard-edit-reopen.png` and `workboard-drag-running-persisted.png`. Videos: `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/workboard/workboard-writable.webm` and `workboard-read-only.webm`.\n\nObserved result after fix: The browser flow showed the Workboard loading with enabled config, opened the new-card modal, selected custom dropdown options, created and edited cards, opened details, dragged a card to Running, synced lifecycle to Review, refreshed without losing the reviewed card, and verified read-only mode hides write actions. The status-persistence E2E also reopened the edit modal and verified custom-select priority state survives before dragging the card.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live production Gateway with private user data was not used; the proof intentionally uses deterministic mocked Gateway data and no secrets.\n",
